Colombian Stocks: Almacenes Exito, ISA Fall; Coltejer Gains

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-05T20:31:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/colombian-stocks-almacenes-exito-isa-fall-coltejer-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 1.8 percent to 13,210.79, while the
Colcap Index fell 1.9 percent to 1,610.98.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest retailer,
fell 2.3 percent to 22,480 pesos, a one-month low. The company
said it began offering 2.5 trillion pesos ($1.4 billion) of
shares today in a sale that will end Sept. 23, according to an
e-mailed statement. The Medellin-based company is offering 114
million shares at 21,900 pesos each, the statement said.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , a Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, gained 2 percent to 1.02 peso. The U.S. House of
Representatives on Sept. 7 will consider a bill to renew tariff
preferences for developing countries, a step that may ease the
way for free-trade agreements with  South Korea , Colombia and
Panama. Laena Fallon, a spokeswoman for House Majority Leader
 Eric Cantor , a Virginia Republican, outlined plans for the House
vote next week in a Sept. 2 e-mail.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)  , a Colombian
electricity and roadway company, fell 0.2 percent to 12,180
pesos. The company’s Brazilian subsidiary was awarded two lots
in a Sept. 2 transmission concession auction, according to an e-
mailed statement. The concessions include three substations and
four transmission lines, extending the subsidiary’s presence
into Brazil’s Paraiba and Pernambuco states.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
